cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper discusses the properties and loss functions of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and their performance on synthetic and image datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since GANs are a type of neural network, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses the theoretical properties of GANs, cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible sub-category as well.
